{"id":297463367,"lang":"python3","time":"1 year, 6 months","timestamp":1580013149,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"1392 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/297463367/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Perfect Squares","memory":"14.8 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def numSquares(self, n: int) -> int:\n        import math\n        maxi = int(math.sqrt(n))\n        self.cands = [i*i for i in range(1,maxi+1)]\n        self.queue = set([n])\n        self.visited = set([])\n        self.step = 0\n        while True : \n            n = len(self.queue)\n            self.queue_ = set([])\n            if n == 0 :\n                break\n            for i in range(n) : \n                num = self.queue.pop()\n                if num == 0 :\n                    return self.step \n                \n                for cand in self.cands : \n                    cur = num - cand\n                    if cur  >= 0  :  \n                        self.queue_.add(cur)\n                self.visited.add(num)\n            self.step += 1 \n            self.queue = self.queue_\n        return -1 \n\n        ","compare_result":"","title_slug":"perfect-squares"}
